ABCs let you define a formal contract: any subclass **must** implement these methods.

If a subclass does not implement all abstract methods, creating an instance raises `TypeError`.

```python
from abc import ABC, abstractmethod

class Shape(ABC):
    @abstractmethod
    def area(self) -> float:
        ...
